abstract: Alabama’s most populous county sued JPMorgan Chase and others for a financial disaster that brought it to the brink of what would be the nation’s largest municipal bankruptcy.
snippet: Alabama’s most populous county sued JPMorgan Chase and others for a financial disaster that brought it to the brink of what would be the nation’s largest municipal bankruptcy.
lead_paragraph: Even after a $700 million settlement with the federal government, JPMorgan Chase still faces troubles in Alabama.

headline.main: JPMorgan Faces New Suit in Alabama County’s Woes
headline.print_headline: JPMorgan Faces New Suit In Alabama County’s Woes
